explanation: This solution uses a queue to store the timestamps of the requests. For each new request, it removes the requests that are older than 3000 milliseconds from the front of the queue, and then returns the size of the queue, which represents the number of requests in the past 3000 milliseconds. The time complexity is O(1) because the operations on the queue take constant time, and the space complexity is O(1) because the size of the queue is bounded by the number of requests in the past 3000 milliseconds.

